window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>A sensational case. Dark motives. Deadly secrets. </p> <p>When Judge Samuel Chesterfield is found murdered in his chambers during a high-stakes wrongful death trial against a prominent abortionist, suspicion immediately falls on the only four people who had access: the trial lawyers. At the center of the storm is Edward Mead—a brilliant, 77-year-old legal scholar still reeling from the death of his wife.</p> <p>Appointed special prosecutor, Mead must navigate a labyrinth of corruption, deceit, and danger that threatens both his mind and his life.</p> <p>FBI Special Agent Sarah Riehl is desperate to prove herself in a system that’s kept her sidelined. But her relentless pursuit of justice leads her into a deadly game where the hunter becomes the hunted—and the truth could get her killed.</p> <p>Lethal Objection is a gripping legal thriller packed with courtroom intrigue, moral complexity, and nail-biting suspense. For fans of John Grisham, Robert Whitlow, and Agatha Christie.</p>"; 
